  "prompt": "How do you invert your selection in Photoshop?",
  "response": "In Adobe Photoshop, inverting your selection allows you to select everything that is not currently selected. Here\u2019s how to do it:\n\n1. **Make an Initial Selection**: Use any selection tool (like the Marquee Tool, Lasso Tool, or Quick Selection Tool) to create your initial selection.\n\n2. **Invert the Selection**:\n   - Go to the top menu and click on **Select**.\n   - From the dropdown menu, choose **Inverse** (you can also use the keyboard shortcut **Shift + Ctrl + I** on Windows or **Shift + Command + I** on Mac).\n\nNow, everything that was not selected is selected, and vice versa. You can modify or apply effects to your newly inverted selection as needed.",
